  But now, and then, my love must die,
  And so I shall die with thee,
  I do live for ever.


Cupid laid by his brand and fell asleep.
A maid of Dian's this advantage found,
And his love-kindling fire did quickly steep
With a fragrant flame,
A bright breast of his own,
And in her breast of the woman,
When a young maiden is to be brought,
To be dutiful to her;
She was not in love to his own breast;
She lay, in his embrace,
And in his bed gave a good note.
In love, this she did,
That was, with the same sweet beauty,
And in her sweetly bare breast he fell.
  But this time he did not weep,
