Two loves I have, of comfort and despair,
That like two spirits do suggest me still.
My better angel is a man right fair,
When he showeth me how the sweetest and dreary world
As if to my breast were hid.
With his love of my heart, he thus saves me,
In love, as if he had kept me in his heart.
 
  I love him that loveth me; and yet I know
  that love's wrong, and therefore love's love
    can never tell me what he hath in his heart.
                                 


